LIMELIGHT - Lights, Camera, Action ...

This is the fifth drop-down menu found in the main Movieola titlebar.

To use this tool, move the mouse cursor over the word "Limelight" and
left-mouse-click on "Limelight". This will prompt a drop down menu
with the following options :
	
	Lights...	Alt+L
	Environment...
	Paint Options Setup...
	Paint
	Render Options Setup...
	Render	Alt+R


Limelight: is a group of tools used to setup and then render the
scenes created in the Movieola environment. Limelight may be used to
setup rendering options on a full scene or individual objects within a
scene. Normally, different objects will have different rendering
requirements.. Rendering may be done in the background while other
Movieola operations are in progress. Once Limelight is initiated to
render a scene, Movieola may be exited and other system applications
used while Limelight continues to render a Movieola scene..
